cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about a generative model for natural language, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a recurrent neural network and attention mechanism suggests that it may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The canvas memory mechanism and imputation of missing words suggest that it may also fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of a dynamic canvas and potential applications in natural language processing suggest that it may also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
